        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Support z.ai BigModel team usage",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add z.ai Personal/Team usage scope for saved API-token accounts, with account-level BigModel organization and project fields.\n- Keep z.ai team usage on the API-key request path: team quota uses `type=2`, hourly/model usage uses `type=3`, and both send `Bigmodel-Organization` / `Bigmodel-Project` headers.\n- Match the existing per-account organization metadata pattern while keeping z.ai-specific scope/project handling provider-gated so non-z.ai providers are not affected.\n- Add Settings and CLI support for multi-account z.ai team mode, including local draft editing, required org/project validation, config warnings, dashboard routing, and docs.\n\n## Why\nBigModel team Coding Plan usage can return `当前用户不存在coding plan` when queried through the personal quota path. The team quota and hourly usage paths still work with the z.ai API key, but they need the team selector query parameter and both BigModel organization/project headers. This avoids a cookie/session/browser dependency while supporting common personal + team multi-account setups.\n\n## Notes\n- This PR does not add a z.ai browser-cookie, session, or dashboard-login auth path.\n- Personal z.ai accounts explicitly clear team context; explicit team accounts use their own org/project values and do not inherit provider-level team defaults.\n- Existing legacy z.ai Keychain token migration remains only for old API-token storage migration.\n\n## Test Plan\n- `swift test --filter ProvidersPaneCoverageTests`\n- `swift test --filter ConfigValidationTests`\n- `swift test --filter Zai`\n- `swift test --filter ProviderConfigEnvironmentTests`\n- `swift test --filter TokenAccountEnvironmentPrecedenceTests`\n- `swift build --product CodexBarCLI`\n- `swift build --product CodexBar`\n- `make check`\n- `make docs-list`\n- `make test`\n- `git diff --check`\n- Secret/residue scans for real z.ai keys/JWTs, `updateAccountSilently`, and z.ai cookie/session/browser auth leftovers\n",
